        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 5:44AM CDT by NWS Aberdeen SD</headline>
        <description>At 543 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Mina, or 12 miles west of Aberdeen, moving east at
25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Aberdeen, Warner, Leola, Mina Lake Rec Area, Frederick, Bath,
Columbia, Westport, Deerfield Colony, Grassland Colony, Stratford,
Wetonka, Long Lake Colony, Mina, Barnard, Richmond Lake Rec Area, and
Sand Lake Wildlife Refuge.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
